## Protocol deviation

The CLI creates a new model/cache per invocation, so its engine LRU cannot
survive a warm-up.  W-DECODE therefore used the real HTTP server path, which
keeps one model instance and its LRU resident.  The saved 950-token context was
created from `tests/fixtures/experiments/workloads/w_decode_context.txt`; each
leg restored that exact `session.qws` before requesting the same one-turn
continuation.  The model stopped naturally after 234 generated tokens, so
decode timing uses the engine's 233 stepped tokens (`generated - 1`).

Server command (2T; 4T differed only in `OMP_NUM_THREADS`, port, and chat dir):
SNAP=/Users/deepanwadhwa/.samosa/current/model TOKENIZER=/Users/deepanwadhwa/.samosa/current/tokenizer_qwen36.json SAMOSA_CHATS_DIR=/tmp/samosa-e-x1-chats SAMOSA_PHASE_STATS=1 OMP_NUM_THREADS=2 ./qwen36b --serve --port 18642 --queue 0 --tokenizer /Users/deepanwadhwa/.samosa/current/tokenizer_qwen36.json

Request command (with the original session restored before every run):
curl -sS --max-time 120 http://127.0.0.1:18642/v1/chat/completions -H 'content-type: application/json' --data '{"messages":[{"role":"user","content":"Continue with a concise operational reminder."}],"conversation_id":"decode","max_tokens":256,"thinking":"off","temperature":0,"seed":1729,"stream":false}'

